rComments: 1) If you are taking this course because you really want to learn French, then do your self a favor and learn by yourself instead of wasting your money on this prof! 2) If you are taking this course just for credits, AGAIN do your self a favor and take another course instead of letting this prof sink your GPA!

GUYSSSS haha ok so, let me start off by saying, if u decide to not listen in class no worries doesnt matter u wont learn anyways but get ready to do a crap ton of pages in the workbook at the end of the semester. Not only that but the quizzes hell make you do EASY PEASY WOW SO EASY. but heres the kicker, final exam215 questions. Ya. That many.

So FLS 1513 is a beginner French grammar course. My positives: he is relaxed, eager to answer questions and lets you know well in advance if class was cancelled that day. - It was fully online through zoom, classes were two and a half hours each week. I wasn't aligned with his teaching strategies. But he is trying his best during COVID.
Is a bit shy to correct errors of students. He also makes a lot of mistakes and corrects himself which is confusing.

Dr. Alshtaiwi is a very kind French professor. His assignments and exams were relatively easy for those who already had experience in the French language. He heavily encourages participation in class, since that's the only way you're able to practice your oral speaking. Merci pour un bon trimestre!
